com.koloboke.compile.mutability

Annotation Type Mutable


  • @Retention(value=SOURCE)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface Mutable
    Specifies that Koloboke Compile should generate a mutable (general-purpose) implementation of the annotated class or interface. Element or entry removal operations are allowed in mutable collections.

    This annotation should be applied only for source code self-documentation purposes, because not applying any of the annotations from the com.koloboke.compile.mutability package has the same effect.

    See Also:
    Updatable
